"Here's your medium-level Python coding question:\n\n```\n{\n    \"title\": \"Validating Mountain Arrays (Medium)\",\n    \"description\": \"A mountain array is an array that is first increasing, then decreasing. Write a function `validate_mountain_array` that checks if the given array is a mountain array.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef validate_mountain_array(arr: list[int)) -> bool:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `arr` (list[int]): A list of integers representing the array to be validated.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns `True` if the input array is a mountain array, `False` otherwise.\\n\",\n    \"code\": \"\"\"\ndef validate_mountain_array(arr: list[int)) -> bool:\n    # Check if the array has at least 3 elements\n    if len(arr) < 3:\n        return False\n    \n    # Initialize variables to track increasing and decreasing sequences\n    increasing = True\n    decreasing = False\n    \n    for i in range(1, len(arr)):\n        # If the array is increasing up to this point, check if it starts decreasing after this point\n        if increasing and arr[i] > arr[i - 1]:\n            decreasing = True\n        # If the array was previously increasing but now starts decreasing, it cannot be a mountain array\n        elif not increasing and arr[i] < arr[i - 1]:\n            return False\n        \n        # Update whether we're currently increasing or decreasing\n        if arr[i] > arr[i - 1]:\n            increasing = True\n        else:\n            increasing = False\n    \n    # If the array was increasing up to some point, then decreased from that point onwards, it's a mountain array\n    return not decreasing and decreasing\n\"\"\",\n    \"tests\": [\n        \"assert validate_mountain_array([2, 1]) == False\",\n        \"assert validate_mountain_array([5, 8, 10, 6, 4, 3, 2, 0]) == True\",\n        \"assert validate_mountain_array([1, 2, 3]) == False\",\n        \"assert validate_mountain_array([1, 3, 2, 1]) == False\"\n    ]\n}\n```"